http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Bus-has-valid-fitness-certificate/article13989799.ece

The 50-seater private stage carrier from the State capital that overturned in Tamil Nadu’s Tirunelveli district on Friday morning had valid fitness certificate and registration till August 2016.Regional Transport Officer, Thiruvananthapuram, Thulaseedharan Pillai said the preliminary inquiry had revealed there was no mechanical failure.“The officials who inspected the vehicle that was recovered using crane had told me that the driver might have slept while the bus was cruising along South Valliyur, 40 km from Tirunelveli town,” he said.The MVD officials are yet to ascertain whether the bus or the driver was involved in any major road accidents earlier.Unconfirmed reports reaching here said the accident happened when the driver suddenly turned the bus to avoid hitting a water tank after he lost control of the vehicle. The 2011-make bus was coming from Karaikal to Kerala.